<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 10:15AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...Locally dense fog near Lake Ontario and the Niagara River...
Areas of locally dense fog has formed over portions of Niagara
county and far northern Erie county, including Niagara Falls and
Grand Island, with visibilities a quarter mile or less. These low
visibilities will continue through the rest of the morning and
could last into the early afternoon.
If traveling near Lake Ontario or near the Niagara River,
including I-190 and Route 18 be prepared for rapidly changing
visibilities, slow down, and leave plenty of space between
vehicles.</description>
